# circleci_webhook (Resource)

Manages a CircleCI webhook. Webhooks send HTTP POST payloads to a configured URL when specific events occur in a project.

## Example Usage

```terraform
resource "circleci_webhook" "example" {
  name           = "my-webhook"
  url            = "https://example.com/webhook"
  signing_secret = "my-signing-secret"
  scope_id       = "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
  scope_type     = "project"
  events         = ["workflow-completed", "job-completed"]
  verify_tls     = true
}
```

{{ .SchemaMarkdown | trimspace }}

## Import

Import is supported using `scope_id/webhook_id`:

```shell
terraform import circleci_webhook.example "<scope_id>/<webhook_id>"
```

After import, `scope_type` is automatically set to `"project"` (the only currently supported value).
